<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-07-25T07:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-07-25T07:44:00-05:00" n="305" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/51: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-07-25T12:00:00-00:44">July 25,
                                1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:40 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Referring to the Department’s 25, July 23, 6 p.m. Note had been presented
                            by me without change. See my July 24, noon, and July 24, 10 p.m. Liberia
                            awaiting your observations.</p>
                        <p>Barclay agrees that you announce at this time that the Liberian
                            Government, disturbed by reports regarding labor conditions in Liberia,
                            are appointing an International Commission to investigate matters on the
                            spot. He adds that he will also make announcement.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>